        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 4:34PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 434 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong cluster of
thunderstorms 4 miles northwest of Washburn, or 12 miles east of
Amarillo, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amarillo, Panhandle, Claude, Groom, Washburn, Goodnight, and Pantex.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
